document.title: 2023 Indiana Academic Standards: Kindergarten - Grade 5 Physical Education

707655A6F5E84A039090580AAB0EE852.description: Recognizes that physical activity can help develop friendships.

AFA60F83D4A24C359FD99D4237055B98.description: Identifies physical activities that are enjoyable.

ECA4711BC8AA4E529562F0E69AF5E339.description: Understands that some physical activities are challenging.

D9535CA2E0CD4F9D8FFAD7B58895D42F.description: Recognizes that physical activity is important for good health.

932F393ACF6946F4A2BB8D62E814D511.description: Valuing Health, Enjoyment, Challenge, Self Expression, and Social Interaction

7E123A65875E4973A2143F41F25501F4.description:
The physically literate individual recognizes the value of physical activity for health,
enjoyment, challenge, self expression and/or social interaction.

C2BB4D8C1DDB4F139F3C4B8F83DEFAF4.description:
Follows teacher directions for safe participation and proper use of equipment
with minimal reminders.

9491F9C801964144A61C19020C0E9C27.description: Recognizes the established protocols for class activities.

C36652B951154A3B9C9B483A59A6D763.description: Shares equipment and space with others.

4FA7E4494C1549B3BFD774C9B4AC7D3E.description:
Follows directions in group settings (such as safe behaviors, following rules,
taking turns).

8687BDF8F0564E97952EA1AEC856C13B.description:
The physically literate individual exhibits responsible personal and social behavior
that respects self and others.

947464D8952047999F999D5CB09C9BA0.description:
Identifies health and unhealthy foods and recognizes that food provides
energy for physical activity.

E07653DB8F424F9980AF015A5FA5BA70.description:
Recognizes basic structure and function of body systems (such as the heart
is a muscle, bones make up the skeletal system).

948BD1321AB5494C95F361D14FACED34.description: Developmentally appropriate/ emerging outcomes first appear in grade three.

1707B9489585428CB4201EF9F7FD3FDA.description:
Recognizes that when you move fast, your heart beats faster and you
breathe faster.

B78F2D79346F418B9F1382EFB68DA441.description: Actively participates in physical education class.

7F3B30059AF147ECA933571A3606DB19.description: Recognizes active play opportunities outside physical education class.

B2D5EA334CFE4EBF9B6CCC5E090C9F3E.description:
The physically literate individual demonstrates the knowledge and skills to achieve
and maintain a health-enhancing level of physical activity and fitness.

A1D97962B3ED42B387BD84854EDFF8CC.description: Developmentally appropriate/ emerging outcomes first appear in grade three

A588713E18CB4F2E962E6ACB19AB3131.description:
Travels in general space with different speeds (such as traveling at various
speeds in skill development activities).

401516F81FDE4E85828591DB5F258851.description:
Travels in three different pathways (such as moving in various patterns: straight,
curved).

4BBE12935565419E88A949360F3BA128.description: Moves in personal space to a rhythm.

12647943061448D39889E65B39FBD6C8.description:
Differentiates between movement in personal space and general space at a slow
to moderate speed.

172A3E4B8923480490D528EFAB50D1DC.description:
The physically literate individual applies knowledge of concepts, principles,
strategies and tactics related to movement and performance.

660A5C15C7B445B5841D2F3A9E5D401C.description:
Practices single and group jump roping frequently after watching the activities
modeled for them.

248EA3E9169141009E32108955947439.description: Strikes a lightweight object with a paddle or short-handled racket

906C19EE25EF47CF836087F148651FD6.description:
Volley a lightweight object (such as a balloon), sending it upward with an open
palm.

374E2A2E244E4FC7A2CD75D00DC366FE.description: Performs emerging pattern while receiving with the preferred foot when stationary.

9B92A957BD5E443B94517DEFD57845FC.description: Soft taps a ball using the inside of the foot, sending it forward.

F7B4DCE239904CA5A7B79B31A91268BD.description:
Demonstrates an emerging pattern while passing or kicking from a stationary
position, demonstrating two of the five critical elements of a mature kicking pattern.

4C317231649646E99867BEB7BB3323C7.description: Dribbles a ball with one hand, attempting the second contact.

F605413B3FE74BC39DCCAB804DC4768E.description: Catches a large ball tossed by a skilled thrower.

DDA434B21EF44AA98373D4DC6ADE0FA2.description: Drops a ball and catches it before it bounces twice.

23C5F5A00F194418BC40D637BADE5E89.description: Developmentally appropriate/emerging outcomes first appear in grade four.

5C4ABB4AB7C048409467EA73DBD23125.description:
Throws underhand and overhand with opposite foot forward demonstrating an
emerging pattern.

4883A4E379E74A10884565C891C39F67.description: Developmentally appropriate/emerging outcomes first appear in grade one.

C5D93A8283234335B1E46B8D62565F93.description:
Maintains momentary balance (such as wide, narrow, curled and twisted body
shapes) on different bases of support (such as walking on the floor).

2737B29F7D5D41F9ACF22E5AC1A50AEC.description:
Performs emerging patterns in nonlocomotor skills (such as bend, twist, turn, sway,
stretch) in exploratory and a stable environment.

0E530EA7EC644942AB1AD6997A5ABFC6.description: Performs dance (rhythmic) activities in response to teacher led creative activities.

2726EBFAAD304591A80A1DB70FD39641.description:
Performs jumping and landing actions with balance (such as when you hear the
color of your shirt, jump over a line on the floor).

B43D2CAFE514433A9181B644F1711ACA.description: Locomotor (Jumping and landing in a horizontal and vertical plane)

5E67600A35C843FA8A1F65F223AFFA6F.description: Perform mature patterns in locomotor skills (walk).

00DD47085A9B43D3BF5BA41F92FDDB9F.description:
Performs emerging patterns in locomotor skills (walk, run, leap, hop, gallop, slide,
and skip) while maintaining balance (such as when you hear the color of your shirt leap
over a pillow).

EB417DEBC8F34F75B7C2BB267108A38C.description: Locomotor (Hopping, galloping, running, sliding, skipping, leaping, walking, running)

5376E7E3CC304B1A9149E3929F67EC3A.description:
The physically literate individual will demonstrate competency in a variety of motor
skills and movement patterns.
